However, you're aware how friends can be—they seldom accept a refusal. Thus, she prodded me slightly. Emerging from the water, I saw a frog perched on the bank. And I burst into laughter—helplessly. Just be patient, I declared, the time for your plunge is imminent!

recall_text: My friend pushed me into a lake. It was at a summer camp. We were all enjoying a peaceful afternoon. She had asked me to catch a frog. I had just sat down to eat my lunch. So I said no. Course friends don't always take no for an answer. So she crept up behind me. And pushed me into the lake. I saw on the shore a frog. Which she picked up. And handed to me. I couldn't help but laugh. Uncontrollably.
